                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d467">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851.248/302: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bullitt</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-11-28T16:00:00+00:00"
                            >November 28, 1939—4 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 4:22 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>2844. I communicated the substance of your No. 1443, November 25, 3 p.m., gently
                    to Daladier today. He said that he understood but could not escape from the
                    conclusion that it would be essential for me to make such a trip in the month of
                    January. I left the matter there.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bullitt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
